org.obapanel.jedis.cache.simple

Interface CacheWriter


  • public interface CacheWriter
    Used to give a cache write-through capabilities or when storing data into a cache, to also store in external sources (like a database)

      • write

        default void write(java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> entry)

        Parameters:

      • writeAll

        default void writeAll(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> values)
        Write the specified entries to the external resource. This method is intended to support both insert and update. A default, looping, non-optimized implementation is provided
        Parameters:
        values - a collection to write.

      • delete

        Delete the cache entry from the external resource.
        Parameters:

      • deleteAll

        default void deleteAll(java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> keys)
        Remove data and keys from the external resource for the given collection of keys, if present. A default, looping, non-optimized implementation is provided
        Parameters:
        keys - a collection of keys for entries to delete.
